Yash PratapYash Pratap • YouVerified • You Web Dev, System Design, AI | Social ScienceWeb Dev, System Design, AI | Social Science 1mo • Edited • 1 month ago • Edited • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn
Is the Indian Economy Actually Dead?

I don't think this question reflects what’s really happening.

India’s macroeconomic indicators show steady growth, rarely going negative, but the real question is—how useful is this growth for the majority?

Our credibility with global institutions like the World Bank and UN has improved over the past three decades, regardless of the government in power.

Both India and Pakistan have grown, but India’s growth has been stronger and more stable.

For the bottom 100 crore Indians and 20 crore Pakistanis, life has improved, but progress remains slow and uneven.

So, what is exactly dead?

It's the social mobility of Urban India except upper middle class and riches.

For India, it's the top 10 crore people except the top 28 lakh (25LPA+ INR salary).

For Pakistan, it's the top 0.7 crore people except the top 0.9 lakh (20LPA+ INR (50LPA PKR) salary).

Crony capitalism is needed to boost the economy but only works with better infrastructure.

For Pakistan, they just sold their assets and even the critical sectors to China and Europe.

For India, they just sold everything to Adani and other Indian cronies, but still, India has the control.

All this unethical stuff was done to protect India from outside and improve the lives of the top 30 lakh people and their family members at the expense of the majority of Urban India's growth.

Here is where the real blunder happened—the real miscalculations.

The world became more connected, and the Indian upper middle class became relatively more open-minded due to internet access and better education.

Without major improvements in urban infrastructure and policy reforms, the quality of life in India dropped significantly,

These top 30 lakh Indian and their family members prioritize "peace of mind in a developed country" over becoming a "demi-god in India under parental control" psychologically resulting in massive immigration among them and their family members to foreign countries at a very high rate (10% of them left India) in past decade.

So, the leverage created by this injustice is lost and has backfired, and the government is clueless now.

The opposition has started doing journalism due to the death of journalism in India.

Now left wing and right wing are no longer interacting, leaving Urban India clueless.

Despite everything, on paper, India is rising just like Pakistan if we ignore the nuance.

So, what is actually dying?

It's the dream of India's self-reliance, confidence, and quality of life in Urban India.

We can't blindly copy the US, China, or any other growth model because India's demography is different.

Saying good or bad things about Trump won't change anything—India needs its own plan designed for its own demography.


hashtag#Trump hashtag#UrbanIndia hashtag#Economy hashtag#Dead
